"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706111","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-08","<p>​The UK supports maintaining the current restrictive measures against Belarus.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-03-08T16:31:05.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706111/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706111/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706111/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-28","Belarus: Sanctions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on the maintenance of (a) the current EU arms embargo on Belarus and (b) EU-imposed travel bans and asset freezes in place in relation to certain specified Belarusian nationals.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","65871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706113","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-08","<p>​Some improvements were observed in the conduct of the September 2016 parliamentary elections in Belarus. Two opposition candidates were elected for the first time, but the elections remained a managed affair, key Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights (ODIHR) recommendations remain outstanding and a number of long-standing systemic shortcomings remain.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","65869","2017-03-08T16:26:09.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706113/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706113/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706113/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-28","Belarus: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the progress made by the Government of Belarus in implementing the recommendations of the final report of the OSCE Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights on the conduct of that country's presidential elections in October 2015.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","65880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706114","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-08","<p>Belarus resumed WTO membership negotiations in January 2017 when the WTO Working Party on the country’s accession met for the first time in 12 years. Belarus emphasised that moving forward with WTO accession is a priority for the country in 2017. It has concluded bilateral market access agreements with 10 WTO members to date.</p><p>Although a core member of the Eurasian Economic Union, the dividends that Belarus must reasonably have hoped to gain from its membership have not materialised. Trade amongst the EEU countries has fallen: by 11% in 2014 and by 25% in 2015.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","65863","2017-03-08T17:02:09.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706114/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706114/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706114/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-28","Belarus: Eurasian Economic Union","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Belarusian counterpart on the effects of Eurasian Economic Union membership on the economic performance of that country.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","65890"
