"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706267","Scotland Office","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Scotland Office spend on iPads and tablets over the last five financial years is shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spend</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p>0.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p>0.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p>0.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p>0.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td><td><p>£1,736.67</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Spend on paper is not separately recorded from other stationery costs and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-03-07T16:13:23.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706267/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706267/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-02-28","Scotland Office: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much his Department spent on (a) iPads and tablets and (b) paper in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","65991"
