"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706293","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-03-06","<p>The Government has considered the potential for molten salt reactor technology to contribute to the UK’s energy mix. In 2014 Innovate UK funded a study examining the feasibility of developing a pilot scale reactor for six molten salt reactor designs. In 2015 the Government commissioned the Techno-Economic Assessment of Small Modular Reactors (SMRs), to which a molten salt reactor developer contributed evidence. There are currently a number of molten salt reactor vendors participating in the UK SMR Competition and Government officials have met with them to discuss their proposals.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-03-06T13:34:21.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706293/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706293/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-02-28","Nuclear Reactors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government has researched the use of stable salt reactor technology as part of the UK's energy mix.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","65932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706294","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-08","<p>I refer the hon Member for St Albans to the answer given by my Rt. Hon Friend the Minister of State for International Trade (Greg Hands) on 27 February 2017, UIN: 64023. Answer included below:</p><p>The import, export and placing on the market of cat and dog fur, and products made from such fur is prohibited under EU legislation (Council Regulation (EC) No 1523/2007). As part of our exit from the EU and through the Great Repeal Bill, these controls will be carried over into UK law.</p><p>Border Force will act to enforce the legislation if illegal cat and dog fur products are detected during the course of carrying out other customs import and export checks, or following receipt of specific intelligence. In these cases, samples are taken and forensically examined. Consignments are seized where they are confirmed to contain cat or dog fur.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-03-08T17:52:16.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706294/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706294/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-28","Furs: Smuggling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 27 February 2017 to Question 64007, whether his Department is able to identify domestic cat and dog fur from non-domestic cat and dog fur that enters or is sold in the UK; and whether he plans to introduce regulatory proposals to include non-domestic cat and dog fur currently not covered by Council Regulation (EC) No 1523/2007 after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","65940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706295","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-08","<p>The Department for International Trade is newly formed and became a legal entity on November 9<sup>th</sup> 2016. Since this date our Digital and IT teams have not purchased any tablets or iPads for the Department.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-03-08T17:56:18.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706295/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706295/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-28","Department for International Trade: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much his Department spent on (a) iPads and tablets and (b) paper in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","65988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706296","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-03-07","<p>Information on expenditure on (a) ipads and tablets and (b) paper is not separately identifiable on the departmental accounting system. The Department was created in July 2016, so there was no expenditure in prior years.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-03-07T17:57:48.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706296/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706296/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-02-28","Department for Exiting the European Union: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how much his Department has spent on (a) iPads and tablets and (b) paper since it was established.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","65983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706297","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-03-06","<p>The White Paper sets out the Government's approach to forging a new strategic partnership between the United Kingdom and the EU. The Department for Exiting the European Union coordinates policy work across Government and works closely with officials in departments on all of its work, including the White Paper. <br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","65961 ; 65962 ; 65963 ; 65964 ; 65965 ; 65966 ; 65967","2017-03-06T14:56:02.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706297/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/706297/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-02-28","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what consultations his Department had with the Department for Culture, Media and Sport on the drafting of the White Paper entitled the United Kingdom's exit from and new partnership with the European Union, Cm 9417, published in February 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","65960"
