"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705547","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-07","<p>Information on DCMS’s procurement spend is set out in our annual report for each year. These reports can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-03-07T11:21:17.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705547/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705547/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-27","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the procurement spend of her Department was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705548","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) procures an extensive and complex range of products, covering vests and washers through to armoured vehicles and nuclear submarines. This procurement is managed through a number of Top Level Budget Holders, and the consolidated details of the total procurement spend is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>Full details of the Department's spend can be found in the MOD Annual Report and Accounts, published at; https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/mod-annual-reports</p><p>Information on the Equipment Programme planned spend is available in the annual Defence Equipment Plan, published at; https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-defence-equipment-plan-2016</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-07T15:12:36.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705548/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705548/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the procurement spend of his Department was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705549","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-06","<p>As set out in the recent White Paper, the United Kingdom's exit from and new partnership with the European Union (Cm9417) dated February 2017, the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States our future status and arrangements with regard to EU agencies. It would not be appropriate to prejudge the outcome of the negotiations.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-06T17:23:43.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705549/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705549/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what (a) EU agencies and other organisations within his Department's remit the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU, (b) staff time was spent on engagement with those bodies and (c) financial resources were spent on engagement with those bodies in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705550","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-06","<p>The Nuclear Weapons Safety Committee no longer exists. The Warhead Safety Co-ordinating Committee ceased to exist in 1993.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","65704","2017-03-06T17:20:54.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705550/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705550/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Nuclear Weapons Safety Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, (a) what the terms of reference are, (b) how many members there are, (c) who the current chair is, (d) what the date of the last meeting was and (e) what the date of the next meeting is of the Nuclear Weapons Safety Committee.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","65699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705551","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-06","<p>It is Ministry of Defence policy that we do not comment on the operational details of convoys transporting Defence Nuclear Material, for the purpose of safeguarding national security.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-06T16:10:10.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705551/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705551/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many days in 2016 Special Escort Group's armoured protected patrol vehicles were unavailable for service.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","65703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705552","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-06","<p>The Nuclear Weapons Safety Committee no longer exists. The Warhead Safety Co-ordinating Committee ceased to exist in 1993.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","65699","2017-03-06T17:20:53.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705552/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705552/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) accidents, (b) incidents and (c) near misses have been reported to the (i) Nuclear Weapons Safety Committee and (ii) Warhead Safety Co-ordinating Committee in each year since 2005; and if he will provide details of any such incidents.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","65704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705553","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-02","<p>No UK military personnel are currently stationed in Yemen.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-02T16:05:59.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705553/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705553/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Yemen: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel of each service of the armed forces are stationed in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","65581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705554","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-02","<p>There are no members of the Royal Military Police working on Iraq Historic Allegations Team (IHAT) investigations. All IHAT investigations are the responsibility of the Royal Navy Police.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-02T16:06:27.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705554/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705554/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Iraq Historic Allegations Team","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many members of the Royal Military Police are working on Iraq Historic Allegations Team investigations.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","65628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705555","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-02","<p>The Virtus system was fully and successfully evaluated during extensive human factors, equipment and vehicle compatibility trials.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-02T16:05:23.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705555/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705555/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Armed Forces: Body Armour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effect that Virtus body armour has on the ability of service personnel to use (a) equipment and (b) vehicles effectively.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","65606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705556","Ministry of Defence","true","2017-03-02","<p>There have been 20,407 sets of Virtus body armour issued, with further sets to be issued, and the full operating capability for Virtus to occur in <del class="ministerial">2015</del><ins class="ministerial">2025</ins>.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-02T16:04:47.727Z","2017-03-06T10:17:04.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705556/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705556/answer","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705556/answer/previousversion/37994","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-27","Armed Forces: Body Armour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he expects the roll-out of Virtus body armour to be complete.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","65607"
