"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705573","Department for Education","false","2017-03-04","<p>As set out in the recent White Paper (The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union), the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States our future status and arrangements with regard to EU agencies. It would not be appropriate to prejudge the outcome of the negotiations.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-03-04T09:44:20.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705573/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705573/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705573/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-27","Department for Education: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what (a) EU agencies and other organisations within her Department's remit the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU, (b) staff time was spent on engagement with those bodies and (c) financial resources were spent on engagement with those bodies in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705574","Department for Education","false","2017-03-02","<p>The Skills Funding Agency has identified possible alternative providers for all Advanced Learner Loans funded learners previously at John Frank Training Limited. The transfer process is progressing with learner involvement.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2017-03-02T17:46:21.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705574/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705574/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705574/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-27","Adult Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what discussions she has had with the Skills Funding Agency on its attempts to find alternative providers for adult learners affected by the liquidation of John Frank Training.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","65746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705575","Department for Education","false","2017-03-02","<p>Our priority is to help ensure learners can continue with their courses with minimal disruption. We are actively working with the Skills Funding Agency and Student Loans Company to identify suitable alternative training providers or colleges with whom learners can complete their studies, and to ensure they do not lose out from any transfer. We are committed to finding a solution for each learner and making the process as smooth as possible.</p><p> </p><p>Where there may ultimately be no viable alternative providers available for some learners to complete their study, we will consider what might be done to avoid these learners being unfairly disadvantaged.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2017-03-02T17:48:18.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705575/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705575/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705575/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-27","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will meet with the (a) Skills Funding Agency and (b) Student Loan Company to discuss the feasibility of writing off student loan debts for adult students unable to continue courses as a result of the failure of the course provider.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","65747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705576","Department for Education","false","2017-03-02","<p>The Skills Funding Agency and the Student Loans Company regularly provide details to the Department on the number of learners that were studying at providers that no longer are operating in the loans programme. Those providers represent only 1% of the total number of providers.</p><p> </p><p>The number of learners currently affected is around 400. The transfer process is progressing with learner involvement and our priority is to support learners to complete their learning. We are monitoring on a weekly basis as learners are transferred to new providers.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon","65748","2017-03-02T17:36:44.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705576/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705576/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705576/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-27","Adult Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the number of adult learners who are currently without a provider to complete their qualifications.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","65745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705577","Department for Education","false","2017-03-07","<p>Procurement spend for the Department for Education and its agencies since 2010 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year ending</p></td><td><p>£millions</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>509</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>533</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>286</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>325</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>390</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>397</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>415</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017 to Sept 2016</p></td><td><p>254</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-03-07T15:40:56.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705577/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705577/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-27","Department for Education: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the procurement spend of her Department was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65682"
