 Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-03-07T15:31:27.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705709/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705709/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-27","Department for Transport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the procurement spend of his Department was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705710","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-07","<p>As set out in the recent White Paper (The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union), the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States our future status and arrangements with regard to EU agencies. It would not be appropriate to prejudge the outcome of the negotiations.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-03-07T17:07:17.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705710/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705710/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-27","Department for Transport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what (a) EU agencies and other organisations within his Department's remit the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU, (b) staff time was spent on engagement with those bodies and (c) financial resources were spent on engagement with those bodies in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705711","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-07","<p>The pricing of insurance products is a commercial decision for individual insurers based on their assessment of the level of risk posed by a given applicant and the Government does not seek to intervene. The Department for Transport has held a number of meetings with the motor insurance industry, for example, to discuss technological measures which have the potential to bear down on the cost of insurance.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has brought forward measures to reduce the excessive costs arising from unnecessary whiplash claims, and expects average savings of £40 to £50 per motor insurance policy. The motor insurance market is intensively competitive and the Government therefore expects that the insurance industry will pass on savings to consumers.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-03-07T13:48:03.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705711/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705711/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705711/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-02-27","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to (a) reduce variation in car insurance premiums between different parts of the UK and (b) ensure that people are not being charged a higher premium for living in a poorer area.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","65813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705712","Wales Office","false","2017-03-06","<p>As set out in the recent White Paper (The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union), the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States our future status and arrangements with regard to EU agencies. It would not be appropriate to prejudge the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-03-06T15:58:28.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705712/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705712/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-02-27","Wales Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what (a) EU agencies and other organisations within his Department's remit the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU, (b) staff time was spent on engagement with those bodies and (c) financial resources were spent on engagement with those bodies in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705713","Wales Office","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Wales Office receives procurement services from the Ministry of Justice. We therefore do not hold the information that you have requested.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-03-07T11:43:10.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705713/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705713/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-02-27","Wales Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what the procurement spend of his Department was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705714","Wales Office","false","2017-03-07","<p>The UK Government is working constructively with local partners and the Welsh Government towards a city deal for the Swansea Bay city region. I have met regularly with the local team, key stakeholders and private sector partners to discuss progress.</p><p> </p><p>In recent months I have hosted meetings specifically on the City Deal on the following dates:</p><p>1 September 2016;</p><p>14 September 2016;</p><p>7 November 2016;</p><p>5 December 2016;</p><p>6 December 2016;</p><p>17 January 2017; and</p><p>22 February 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, I have had a number of phone calls with strategic partners.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-03-07T11:44:53.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705714/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705714/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-02-27","City Region Deals: Swansea Bay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, if he will publish the dates of all meetings he has had with strategic partners on the proposed Swansea Bay City Region deal.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","65701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705715","Women and Equalities","false","2017-03-07","<p>Procurement spend for the Government Equalities Office for financial year ending 2016 was £3,086,146.66.</p><p>Information on the procurement spend for the four financial years preceding 2015/2016 is not available due to machinery of government changes to the Government Equalities Office.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-03-07T17:09:07.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705715/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705715/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-02-27","Government Equalities Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what the procurement spend of the Government Equalities Office was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705716","Women and Equalities","false","2017-03-04","<p>As set out in the recent White Paper (The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union), the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States our future status and arrangements with regard to EU agencies. It would not be appropriate to prejudge the outcome of the negotiations.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-03-04T09:51:52.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705716/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705716/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-02-27","Government Equalities Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what (a) EU agencies and other organisations within the Government Equalities Office's remit the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU, (b) staff time was spent on engagement with those bodies and (c) financial resources were spent on engagement with those bodies in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65642"
