"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705758","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-03-06","<p>The Department is currently in transition following the announcement of its formation in July last year and the bringing together of the functions of the Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC) along with the business, industrial strategy and innovation functions of the former Department of Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS).</p><p>BEIS constituent departments published details of procurement spend within their Annual Reports (this included spend attributed to higher and further education policy, apprenticeships and skills which have transferred to Department for Education and trade policy and export control, as well as the functions previously performed by UK Trade and Investment which have transferred to the new Department for International Trade). This spend is summarised in the table below:</p><p>£’000</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DECC</p></td><td><p>3,384,658</p></td><td><p>3,454,641</p></td><td><p>3,454,317</p></td><td><p>3,576,766</p></td><td><p>3,749,658</p></td><td><p>3,787,307</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>BIS</p></td><td><p>2,003,877</p></td><td><p>1,548,275</p></td><td><p>1,306,695</p></td><td><p>1,690,665</p></td><td><p>1,499,267</p></td><td><p>1,413,371</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p><strong>5,388,535 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5,002,916 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>4,761,012 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5,267,431 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5,248,925 </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5,200,678 </strong></p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Sources:</em></p><p><em>DECC <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/decc-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">2010-11</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">2011 onwards</a> (Core tables).</em></p><p><em>BIS <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/444895/BIS-15-421-BIS-Annual-Report-15-HI-RES.pdf" target="_blank">2010-11</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/537425/bis-annual-report-accounts-2015-16-web.pdf" target="_blank">2011 onwards</a> (Annex A).</em></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-03-06T13:34:06.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705758/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705758/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-02-27","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the procurement spend of his Department was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705759","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-03-06","<p>As set out in the recent White Paper (The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union), the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States our future status and arrangements with regard to EU agencies. It would not be appropriate to prejudge the outcome of the negotiations.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-03-06T14:19:26.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705759/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705759/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-02-27","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what (a) EU agencies and other organisations within his Department's remit the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU, (b) staff time was spent on engagement with those bodies and (c) financial resources were spent on engagement with those bodies in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705760","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-02","<p>The Department for International Trade will engage with stakeholders over the coming weeks and months, and Parliament will have an important role to play in future UK trade deals. In line with normal international diplomatic practice, it would not be appropriate to routinely provide details of private diplomatic engagement with foreign governments.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-02T17:44:37.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705760/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705760/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans he has to provide information regularly to (a) hon. Members and (b) the public on the progress of those trade working groups which have been established in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","65670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705761","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-02","<p>Ministers and officials in the Department for International Trade are working closely with counterparts across a wide range of markets, in order to promote the UK as a great place to do business and with which to trade. We have announced nine working groups in the last 12 months: with Australia, China, the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC), Israel, India, New Zealand, Norway, Turkey and South Korea. The GCC comprises 6 countries: Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, and the UAE. As the PM announced during her visit to Washington, we will also take forward high-level talks with the USA.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-02T13:50:14.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705761/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705761/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with which countries he has established trade working groups in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","65671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705762","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-02","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave on the 2 February to my hon Friend for South Basildon and East Thurrock, UIN 61710.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-02T13:51:59.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705762/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705762/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Government Chief Scientific Adviser","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he plans to appoint a Chief Science Adviser prior to the opening of negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","65660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705763","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) was not formed in 2010, the transfer of functions order established DIT as a corporation sole on 9 November 2016. The Department will publish its full annual report and accounts for the first time after the financial year end on the 31<sup>st</sup> March 2017. We are working to collate data for the whole department in order to meet transparency requirements on central government spend.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-07T14:55:01.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705763/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705763/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Department for International Trade: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the procurement spend of his Department was in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","65690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705764","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-02","<p>Treaties, including CETA, that are subject to ratification, approval, acceptance, accession or the mutual notification of completion of procedures are typically laid before Parliament for scrutiny purposes for a period of 21 parliamentary sitting days under the provisions of the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010 (Part 2: ratification of treaties), which commenced on 11 November 2010. This legislation provides that the UK cannot legally ratify or consent to be bound by a treaty laid under its provisions until the statutory 21 sitting day process has elapsed. During the 21 sitting days, hon Members and Select Committees have the chance to scrutinise the treaty provisions, ask questions, and potentially report.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-02T17:29:51.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705764/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705764/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, following the debate at European Committee B on 6 February 2017, and vote taken as division 151 on 8 February 2017, what further opportunities he expects Parliament to have to scrutinise the EU-Canada Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement before the agreement is ratified by the UK.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","65736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705765","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>As set out in the recent White Paper (The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union), the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States our future status and arrangements with regard to EU agencies. It would not be appropriate to prejudge the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-07T13:11:15.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705765/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705765/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what (a) EU agencies and other organisations within his Department's remit the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU, (b) staff time was spent on engagement with those bodies and (c) financial resources were spent on engagement with those bodies in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705766","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>UK Export Finance is scrutinising the deferred prosecution agreements and statements of facts agreed by the Serious Fraud Office and other overseas investigating authorities with Rolls Royce, in order to consider whether the information contained has any implications for existing support, or more widely.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","65816 ; 65817 ; 65818","2017-03-07T14:59:02.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705766/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705766/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Rolls-Royce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the terms of reference are for the internal review being conducted by UK Export Finance into the support it provided to Rolls-Royce.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","65723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705767","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>UK Export Finance is scrutinising the deferred prosecution agreements and statements of facts agreed by the Serious Fraud Office and other overseas investigating authorities with Rolls Royce, in order to consider whether the information contained has any implications for existing support, or more widely.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","65723 ; 65816 ; 65818","2017-03-07T14:59:02.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705767/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705767/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Rolls-Royce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many officials in UK Export Finance are involved in conducting the review into its support for Rolls-Royce; and who is heading that review.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","65817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705768","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>UK Export Finance is scrutinising the deferred prosecution agreements and statements of facts agreed by the Serious Fraud Office and other overseas investigating authorities with Rolls Royce, in order to consider whether the information contained has any implications for existing support, or more widely.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","65723 ; 65817 ; 65818","2017-03-07T14:59:02.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705768/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705768/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Rolls-Royce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if officials in UK Export Finance conducting its review into its support for Rolls-Royce will seek information from the Serious Fraud Office.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","65816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705769","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>Details about exporters and amounts supported by UK Export Finance are published annually in its Annual Report and Accounts which is presented to Parliament.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-07T13:09:58.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705769/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705769/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, who the five clients and companies with the highest volume of trade supported by UK Export Finance were in each of the last three financial years.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","65812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705770","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>UK Export Finance is scrutinising the deferred prosecution agreements and statements of facts agreed by the Serious Fraud Office and other overseas investigating authorities with Rolls Royce, in order to consider whether the information contained has any implications for existing support, or more widely.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","65723 ; 65816 ; 65817","2017-03-07T14:59:02.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705770/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705770/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Rolls-Royce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether he plans to make public the report arising out of UK Export Finance's review of its support for Rolls-Royce.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","65818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705771","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Department for International Trade has a strong core of trade policy officials, which has quadrupled in size since 24 June and is continuing to grow. This includes policy and country specialists, as well as economic analysts and lawyers.</p><p> </p><p>To date, recruitment has primarily been from within the Civil Service. We are currently running an external campaign for recruiting high quality individuals with a range of policy, negotiation and trade-specific skills and experience. This external campaign is ongoing.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-03-07T14:53:38.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705771/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705771/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705771/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many trade negotiators are employed by his Department and how many were hired from (a) within the UK civil service, (b) the UK private sector, (c) from within the EU and (d) from outside the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","65788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705772","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) is building on its existing strong core of trade policy expertise. At this stage our primary focus is on developing policy positions, international relationships and our approach to future trade negotiations.</p><p>DIT, in conjunction with the Foreign and Commonwealth Office has established the Trade Policy and Negotiations Faculty, dedicated to building trade policy and negotiations capability across HM Government.</p><p>The Faculty and DIT have already offered a range of training on trade policy:</p><ul><li>Eight 3-hour Trade Foundation Training Programmes, and e-learning modules;</li><li>Nineteen 90-minute trade policy practitioner level masterclasses; and</li><li>42 hours of trade policy practitioner level training, with 21 more hours scheduled for mid-March 2017.</li></ul><p>These training sessions have been attended by over 800 officials from 19 Government departments and agencies.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","65790","2017-03-07T16:45:58.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705772/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705772/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705772/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much his Department has spent on the training of trade negotiators to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","65789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705773","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-07","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) is building on its existing strong core of trade policy expertise. At this stage our primary focus is on developing policy positions, international relationships and our approach to future trade negotiations.</p><p>DIT, in conjunction with the Foreign and Commonwealth Office has established the Trade Policy and Negotiations Faculty, dedicated to building trade policy and negotiations capability across HM Government.</p><p>The Faculty and DIT have already offered a range of training on trade policy:</p><ul><li>Eight 3-hour Trade Foundation Training Programmes, and e-learning modules;</li><li>Nineteen 90-minute trade policy practitioner level masterclasses; and</li><li>42 hours of trade policy practitioner level training, with 21 more hours scheduled for mid-March 2017.</li></ul><p>These training sessions have been attended by over 800 officials from 19 Government departments and agencies.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","65789","2017-03-07T16:45:58.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705773/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705773/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705773/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-02-27","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many hours have been spent on training for trade negotiators since the creation of his Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","65790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705774","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-03-02","<p>The Agreement on a Unified Patent Court is not a treaty which attracts a referendum under the European Union Act 2011.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-03-02T14:47:16.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705774/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705774/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705774/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-02-27","Unified Patent Court","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his Department's policy is on the holding of a referendum under the terms of the European Union Act 2011 prior to ratifying the Agreement on a Unified Patent Court.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","65809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705775","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-03-07","<p>The UK's formal and informal relationship with the EU's decentralised bodies will depend on the negotiations in each area outlined by the Prime Minister's speech. Any analysis of the UK's intended relationship with these bodies would presuppose the UK's preferred outcome and red lines in the negotiation, and Parliament has voted repeatedly not to disclose material that could damage the United Kingdom’s position in its negotiations with the European Union.<br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-03-07T17:55:16.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705775/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/705775/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-02-27","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, which agencies and organisations the Government plans to withdraw from when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","65800"
